    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a driver-focused 2011 BMW M3 featuring the S65B40 naturally aspirated V8. This high-revving 4.0L powerplant utilizes eight individual throttle bodies and a 12.0:1 compression ratio to achieve its 8,400 RPM redline. This example is mechanically robust, with documented preventative maintenance including rod bearing replacement and upgraded throttle actuators. The 7-speed M-DCT provides lightning-fast shifts, while the M-Variable differential and Electronic Damper Control (EDC) ensure precise chassis dynamics. Minor cosmetic wear is present, but the drivetrain remains taut and the visceral induction note is unmatched. A mechanically sound specimen of the last high-revving, atmospheric M3.",
